ZH: 这种荒谬的说法严重物化了女性。
EN: This absurd statement greatly objectifies women.

ZH: 他的言论似乎在物化他人。
EN: His remarks seem to objectify others.

ZH: 别总把人当作物品来物化！
EN: Stop treating people as objects to be objectified!

ZH: 这种性别歧视的言论会导致人物化的结果。
EN: This gender-biased rhetoric will lead to objectification of individuals.

ZH: 他总是喜欢把女性物化成性感的对象。
EN: He always likes to objectify women as sexy objects.

ZH: 社会对美貌有一种倾向，容易导致物化女性。
EN: Society has a tendency towards beauty, which easily leads to objectification of women.

ZH: 电视广告时常以物化的方式展示女性形象。
EN: Television advertisements often portray women in objectified ways.

ZH: 我们应该努力避免将别人物化为性对象。
EN: We should strive to avoid objectifying others as sexual objects.

ZH: 这种工作环境容易导致性别物化。
EN: This work environment tends to lead to gender objectification.

ZH: 某些公司的广告策略很容易物化女性形象。
EN: Some companies' advertising strategies easily objectify women.

ZH: 他总是用一种物化的视角看待女性。
EN: He always looks at women from an objectified perspective.

ZH: 这样的想法会导致性别歧视和物化。
EN: Such ideas can lead to gender discrimination and objectification.

ZH: 让我们共同努力反对对妇女的物化。
EN: Let us work together to combat the objectification of women.

ZH: 这些电影片段对女性的物化程度很高。
EN: These movie clips have a high degree of objectification of women.

ZH: 物化他人会带来严重的后果。
EN: Objectifying others can have serious consequences.

ZH: 这种说法明显是对女性的物化。
EN: This statement clearly objectifies women.

ZH: 公众舆论对他的物化言论进行了广泛谴责。
EN: Public opinion widely condemned his objectifying remarks.

ZH: 对他表达的观点进行批评，是对性别物化的一种抗争。
EN: Criticizing his expressed views is a form of resistance against gender objectification.

ZH: 我们不应该把别人当作物品来物化。
EN: We should not objectify others as objects.

ZH: 那种对女性的物化行为不符合道德价值观。
EN: The objectification of women like that is not in line with moral values.
